00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:39,100
And this result is, in fact, what you get from training the model.

253
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:41,880
So, what about the numbers inside these convolutional kernels?

254
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:43,960
Essentially, these are the parameters of the neural network.

255
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:45,300
The ones we've trained the model to produce.

256
00:08:45,300 --> 00:08:47,660
and then corrected bit by bit through backpropagation.

257
00:08:47,660 --> 00:08:49,020
Now, let's take a look inside.

258
00:08:49,020 --> 00:08:51,020
In fact, there are three other key concepts we need to cover.

259
00:08:51,020 --> 00:08:53,750
First, a crucial concept is the size of the convolutional kernel.

260
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:54,990
So, the size of the convolutional kernel...

261
00:08:54,990 --> 00:08:57,850
This determines the size of the local region the kernel looks at each time.

262
00:08:57,850 --> 00:08:59,930
A common choice might be a 3x3.

263
00:08:59,930 --> 00:09:01,079
or 5x5.

264
00:09:01,079 --> 00:09:02,499
the larger the convolutional kernel is,

265
00:09:02,499 --> 00:09:04,419
the larger the area it scans each time.

266
00:09:04,419 --> 00:09:06,119
so the visible area at one time is larger.

267
00:09:06,119 --> 00:09:07,439
But the thing is, the larger it is...

268
00:09:07,439 --> 00:09:09,599
the more parameters it's going to have.

269
00:09:09,599 --> 00:09:11,359
And the computational load will increase as well.

270
00:09:11,359 --> 00:09:13,419
Nowadays, the 3x3 kernel is the most common choice.

271
00:09:13,419 --> 00:09:14,319
Because they're small enough.

272
00:09:14,319 --> 00:09:14,959
which makes them easy to stack.

273
00:09:16,039 --> 00:09:17,430
So, let's take an example.

274
00:09:17,430 --> 00:09:19,090
So this is a 3x3 one.

275
00:09:19,090 --> 00:09:21,590
So, for example, you can take a look at how it scans the image.

276
00:09:21,590 --> 00:09:22,750
In fact, the first time is right here.

277
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:23,230
The second time, it moves here.

