00:09:35,220 --> 00:09:37,440
So, horizontally, we can only make four moves each time, right?

287
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:39,160
and we get a result for each step.

288
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:41,170
And vertically, it's the same, it can only scan four times.

289
00:09:41,170 --> 00:09:43,370
So, what you end up with is a 4 by 4 matrix.

290
00:09:43,370 --> 00:09:45,710
So, the feature map has actually gotten smaller.

291
00:09:45,710 --> 00:09:48,950
So, this is the difference based on the size of the convolutional kernel.

292
00:09:48,950 --> 00:09:51,450
So, what if my convolutional kernel is 5x5?

293
00:09:51,450 --> 00:09:53,450
So it can only scan twice, right?

294
00:09:53,450 --> 00:09:55,110
and the resulting image will be 2x2.

295
00:09:55,110 --> 00:09:55,790
So it gets smaller.

296
00:09:55,790 --> 00:09:58,770
But at the end of the day, the numbers we get out are all meaningful.

297
00:09:58,770 --> 00:10:01,950
The second factor is actually the stride, or how much it moves each time.

298
00:10:01,950 --> 00:10:04,710
So, what this means is, before, we were just moving it one step at a time by default.

299
00:10:04,710 --> 00:10:05,270
Right?

300
00:10:05,270 --> 00:10:06,750
moving one pixel at a time.

301
00:10:06,750 --> 00:10:09,070
But in reality, I can increase the stride a bit.

302
00:10:09,070 --> 00:10:11,200
So it moves by a larger amount each time.

303
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:14,040
This way, it will skip one position each time, outputting the feature from that location.

304
00:10:14,040 --> 00:10:17,680
the reduction in the height and width of the feature map becomes more pronounced.

305
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:18,760
Let's say, like this.

306
00:10:18,760 --> 00:10:20,160
I'm jumping two at a time.

307
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:21,760
This way, since it can't go any further.

308
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:22,960
and can't move any further.

309
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:25,580
So, we're basically just discarding this feature.

310
00:10:25,580 --> 00:10:26,569
Then we move on to the second one.

311
00:10:26,569 --> 00:10:28,369
Because if it moves two more steps,

