00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:15,260
So, let's say we have a 4x4 image to start with.

339
00:11:15,260 --> 00:11:16,500
So, after I add this border of zeros,

340
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:17,930
so it becomes 6 by 6.

341
00:11:17,930 --> 00:11:19,290
So now it becomes a 6 by 6 image.

342
00:11:19,290 --> 00:11:21,510
And then, we just do the same scanning process as before.

343
00:11:21,510 --> 00:11:23,250
so the output remains 4 by 4.

344
00:11:23,250 --> 00:11:24,579
I started out with a 4x4.

345
00:11:24,579 --> 00:11:26,400
So after scanning, it's still 4x4.

346
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:28,960
This is for a convolutional kernel size of three.

347
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:30,280
So, when we're making that determination,

348
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:32,260
All you have to do is pad the edges of the image with zeros.

349
00:11:32,260 --> 00:11:33,460
This way, it's possible to...

350
00:11:33,460 --> 00:11:35,420
so that the feature map we get from scanning the image...

351
00:11:35,420 --> 00:11:37,100
matches the size of the original image.

352
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:38,900
So, for this, uh...

